cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

This paper is about Named Entity Recognition (NER) using neural methods, which falls under the category of Natural Language Processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes an unsupervised cross-lingual NER model, which involves transfer learning and parameter sharing, indicating that it may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses adversarial learning, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision, suggesting that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper focuses on NER, which is a sub-field of Information Extraction, indicating that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Information Retrieval and Extraction).
